Class MitigationExpiration

java.lang.Object
  sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      sailpoint.object.SailPointObject
          sailpoint.object.MitigationExpiration
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject, sailpoint.tools.xml.XMLReferenceTarget
public class MitigationExpiration
extends SailPointObject

A MitigationExpiration holds information about a business role or entitlement list mitigation for the purpose of executing some action when the mitigation expires.

See Also:
Serialized Form

hasName

public boolean hasName()
Description copied from class: SailPointObject
Return true if the object has a name. This is used by the AbstractSailPointObject and the PersistenceManagers to tell if the name can be used in a search filter.

It is almost always true, but a few classes like log records do not have meaningful names. Consider using ObjectUtil.hasName(SailPointContext, Class) instead

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
Description copied from class: SailPointObject
We override equals so that two objects will compare equal if they have the same database id or unique name, but are different Java objects. This is necessary for Hibernate because caches commonly have to be cleared or objects from one session need to be used to match things loaded in a different session.
